The paper deals with the computational hardness of learning a binary classification task, which is a topic in both cryptography (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of statistical query model (SQ) also suggests a connection to theoretical computer science (cs.DS). The paper also mentions a standard cryptographic assumption, which further supports the connection to cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the mention of efficient algorithms and computational hardness suggests a connection to computational complexity theory (cs.CC).
